-- EU Carbon May Drop to 3.70-4 Euros: New Energy Finance
-- B y   A l e s s a n d r o   V i t e l l i
-- 2013-02-04T12:18:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-04/eu-carbon-may-drop-to-3-70-4-euros-new-energy-finance-correct-.html
(Corrects Feb. CER supply forecast in third bulletpoint.)  James Cooper, London-based analyst at
Bloomberg New Energy Finance, comments on carbon market in e-
mailed note.
* “Steady price declines” for EU permits “may be inevitable”
amid weekly oversupply: Cooper
* December carbon falls 3.9% to 4.17 euros a metric ton,
according to ICE Futures  Europe  in  London . Contracts jumped to
as high as 4.4 euros a ton on Feb. 1.
* UN Certified Emission Reductions supply in Feb. may fall to
about 9.3m metric tons due to high cost of verification and
issuance relative to market price: Cooper  To contact the reporter on this story:
